	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=155684><span id=Scholar>Iindarie</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>47 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hi all,<br>level 26 druid wood elf here wondering how to make enough money. I still don't even have all of my level 24 spells because I ran out of money and decided that it would be better to save for level 29 instead. I also think I am way under-equipped for my level...low AC leather stuff and a fine steel morning star. I have a couple of nice magic items that some very, very kind souls gave to me, but that's it.&nbsp;&nbsp;I don't expect things to be given to me...have no problem working my way up at all as that makes the game fun...but how do I afford it all?  Right now I am in Lake of Ill Omen, and the loot here has been better than areas I've been in, but with spells being around 20pp each I go broke QUICK!  Any suggestions for getting money, or level appropriate quests to obtain armor/weapons etc. would be much appreciated!!!</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
