	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Apr 11th 7:20 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=52194><span id= >Rexz</span></a><br><span id=notbold>183 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.79]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hail fellow Druids,<br><br>Hey Iindarie, you got a lot of good feedback advises from your fellow druids and you can't go wrong with any of the advises. However, two people already made suggestions that I did with my druid when he was also 26. You want to level as fast as possible to 29 and be able to port others. The average donation per port is 20pp and it gets much higher at higher level zones so start porting as soon as possible. You will get experience faster if you group at your level. I took my druid to Frontier Mountain and fought at the Giant Fort when he turned 26. I don't remember the exact prices of the vendor trash they drop there but many of the items the giants drop are worth somewhere between 10pp to 70pp each. The only item you'll keep is the Forest Loop (earring: AC+2 Agi+3 Dex+3 Wis+3). If you get extras and want to sell, they go for about 350pp on my server. You should be able to get from 26 to 29 in a few days. The guy who also said your life will change when you turn 29, he's 100% correct. In fact, when you get higher in levels, you'll get people asking you for a port daily. It gets to a point where you'll figure out why so many higher level druids are almost always anonymous. One final thought to remember, druids &quot;ARE&quot; the best at making money and most of the money you'll make will not come from porting others.<br><br>Tairad Nosaurus<br>50th Ranger<br>47th Druid<br>47th Warrior<br>46th Bard<br>42nd Cleric</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
