	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=141592><span id=Scholar>dabrock</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>72 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.90]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Mammouths are great as posted, but often hunted to death by lots of groups at certain times, as are all good money mobs. Other ideas are: Evil Eyes in the Gorge of King Xeorb as well as Minataurs (axes are worth 5pp to merchants and more to players) and muddites that sometimes carry silver. If you have spirit pouches you can load up on clay and ore as well.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>If you just want money and aren't worried about experience you can hunt bandits in the Karana zones for sashes and bronze.<br><br>Any three of these methods should yeild around 100pp/hour if you aren't fighting down time and other people too much. You can also hit KFC or the gnoll spires in SK for around 50pp or more an hour depending on group size. There is also decent platimum and items worth decent money from the gnolls at the SK entrance of Lake Ratetear. <br><br>Good luck to you.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Apr  9 15:09:09 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
