	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=63996><span id=Scholar>Lord chking</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>79 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.42]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I agree with wolas on most points, but I must disagree with wolas' level for hunting mammoths. I started fear-kiting red mammoths solo at 24th level, with a relatively untwinked druid. It's simple:<br><br>0) Buff yourself with AT LEAST SoW, Skin like Steel, maybe Barbcoat and Strength of Earth<br>1) Track a mammoth<br>2) /assist mammoth to make sure that no one's pulling him to the mammoth plat.<br>3) Snare<br>4) Creeping Crud<br>5) Terrorize Animal<br>6) Careless Lightning until dead<br>6a) You can practice melee on retreating mammy if you desire<br>7) Rinse, repeat<br><br>As a human druid with average CHA, I make about 10pp per mammy tusk (0-2 on each corpse) in Surefall (don't sell to barbarians), and use the mammoth meat for baking. If you get a rib bone, offer it to shamans in the area -- they need it for their totemic gauntlet quest. Try it -- you might like it. Cheers!</p>&nbsp;<br>-- <br>Aybara the Wookiee Swordsman on Tempest<br>Moloch the Trandoshan Master Marksman on Radiant<br>Vicktar the Mon Calamari Master Artisan on Intrepid</td></tr>
