	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145143><span id=Scholar>wolas</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>28 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I was in the same situation as you. I only left my FS Warhammer at lvl 30 to buy a WraithBone Hammer (100pp).<br><br>At 26 you could try South Karanas. Aviaks and gnolls can be good loot. (Gems, FS weapons and some pps). That was enough for me to buy spells and some gear. <br>I also found that at these levels some spells are quite useless like roots (other than lvl 5), charms for animals, pet increase stats, dismiss summoned (unless you hunt summoded creatures)...<br>So dont try to buy everything.<br><br>In SK you could also do the Gem Inlaid gauntlet quest (easy for a druid with TP)and earn 100 150 pp each time.<br><br>At 29 you will get TP spells. Money will become easier but with luclin TPs less people are interested in basic ports. You will have to wait a bit for more asked ports like Dreadlands or Iceclad.&nbsp;&nbsp;Advice: Bind yourself in nexus and begin a nexus / West commons taxi line. You will find some high level peeps there easyly giving 100pp for a port.<br><br>At 29 you can also go to everfrost and hunt Mammoths. Their tusks sell for 8/9pp and they can carry 2 of them. Also as Halas is far away from everything, ports to NK or WC are often asked.<br><br>More money will come later when you will be able to solo Giants...<br><br>----------------------------<br>Wolas<br>44 Wood Elf Druid<br>Antonious Bayle</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
