	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=69206><span id= >dimle</span></a><br><span id=notbold>50 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>People have probably told you this before, but just forget about money.&nbsp;&nbsp;The day you hit level 29, your life will change forever.  People will POUR money on you for ports; you will stuff banks with it, roll in it, spend it, give it away to newbs, drop it on the ground.  Once you can port people around, you will pull in 100-200 pp per hour just by porting, if you go to a high traffic area like WC or especially LOIO.<br><br>Want 500 pp?  Spend a Saturday afternoon porting.  Want 1000 pp?  Spend a couple of nights doing nothing else.<br><br>I was broke, penniless, with nothing, and after I hit 29, within three days I had upped my wisdom by 22 points by upgrading my armor, had 500 pp in the bank, and had twinked three of my alts with decent lowby stuff.<br><br>Forget money.  Just forget it.  Your rich Uncle is going to die and make you wealthy the day you turn 29.<br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
