	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Apr 3rd 7:03 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=89585><span id= >Xandriah</span></a><br><span id=notbold>9 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.33]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hail,<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;   <br>Creating a new character can be a little confusing. Especially now that there are SOOO many classes and races to choose from. First thing you have to decide is, what do u wanna be when you grow up? Do u want to be primarily a caster or tank? or maybe a combination of the two. Do u already have a char or is this ur first one? If you have one ...are you bored &amp; wanting to try something a little different? Alot different?<br><br>I would probably start with...how do you wanna play. As melee or non-melee. My very first char was a high-elf Mage. I played her for a few lvls before I decided,&quot;Naa...this ain't for me. I wanna whack stuff!!&quot; But I did like having a few spells...so I finally started a Paladin. I loved it. I got to be tank...and still could cast, even if my spells weren't great, I had a blast with her. Then a friend with a druid was having an awful time leveling up and asked me to help. So I logged on to their account to play their Druid....And I've been hooked ever since. <br><br>To me, there is nothing less fun in the world of Norrath than starting a new character. Verant has now made it much easier for us though. You have come to the druid forum, so i'm assuming u have a strong interest there. I'd say, go ahead &amp; start ur druid. You'll start with two lvl 1 spells (Skin like wood &amp; ...is it Flame lick or Burst or Flame?)and something to whack with..hehe. A level 1 char has just enuf HP to be glorified rat meat. But after u get to lvl 5 u'll have lots of newbish spells to choose from (gate &amp; harmony included) and be able to start dishing out some minor dmg.<br><br>If u choose a wood elf, u'll start in Kelethin (ahhh..home sweet home) I made a human druid purely because I wanted to be a little different. I was born in Surefall Glade. made my way to Qeynos...whacked there til I got Camo at lv 5 &amp; then went to Kelethin. Antonica has many many good places to fight, I just like Kelethin &amp; wanted to go to Crushbone...which I think is a really good place to lvl til u get in your late teens. Small zone, easy to find a group, zone line is always close... )<br><br>As u lvl up ur gonna get ur TP spells, then group TP...wolf form...really good buffs...&quot;SOW&quot;...make ur own food/drink...nice DOT's....charm animals if that's ur thing...and if u stick with it, eventually change the weather.<br><br>No, ur not going to be the all powerful druid for quite some time...but u will have a blast getting there. I'm in my 40th season and have a long way to go. But I'm having fun getting there. And I think that's the most important factor reguardless of which race/class u decide on. <br><br>Rayni<br>40th season Druid<br>Xegony<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
