	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f10170758165119>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=8&mid=10170758165119>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=10170758165119>RE: How?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=10170758165119#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Mar 25th 12:07 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=6874><span id=Sage>Jijuna</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>82 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.56]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Would assume you are a low lvl druid.&nbsp;&nbsp;At lvl 1 you get Snare spell and a Direct Damage Spell.  You will get better Direct Damage Spells as you level up, always use your best one.  You can kite with those 2 spells but is dangerous cuz of the short duration of snare (you wont get a better snare until your mid lvls) so best way to go is wait till lvl 14 to get Spirit of Wolf spell, which makes you run faster.<br><br>The process is quite simple, use Spirit of Wolf on yourself, use snare on de mobs you want to kite and start running around casting your Direct Damage Spell on it until dead.  Only thing you will have to learn is your timing, sometimes you will stop to recast Direct Damage too close to the mob and it will land a couple of hits on you, other times you will run too far and will have to wait until the mob is in range again, only requires a little time to get use to this and start kiting quite effectively.<br><br>Now quad kiting is a different story, you will have to wait until lvl 34 to get a new kind of spell, this is an Area of effect Direct Damage Spell, which basically hits your target and all the things around it in a small radious.  Learning to get 4 mobs strechted togheter so you can hit them all with your AoE Spell is much more difficult than to learn to kite.  You will have to ensnare them all (ensnare is the upgrade to snare that last longer) and start running circles around them, until you see they are very tied, and I mean VERY tied, shoulder to shoulder is not enough, to be pretty sure you will have to wait until you see them as they were only one mob, later you will learn when they are close enough with practice.  Switchning camera views while you round around them can help a lot to see when they are close enough.  After that just start running around casting the AoE spell on them until they are dead.  This requires to have a good amount of mana for your lvl, so youd better work on getting some wis or mana gear before lvl 34.  Quad kiting is the best exp ANY player can get (including all classes in comparison) so taking time to get that gear worth it.<br><br>Hope this can help you.<br><br>Asuran<br>Lvl 54 wanderer<br> </p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
