	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f101670494783020>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=8&mid=101670494783020>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=101670494783020>RE: Harmony</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=101670494783020#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Mar 21st 5:05 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=87819><span id=Sage>iteck</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>157 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Harmony is an area effect spell that reduces the aggro radius of mobs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Basically if there are two mobs close together and you cast harmony on the one <b>furthest</b> from you, if it works, you should be able to pull the <b>nearest</b> one on its own.<br><br>If you are close enough to see the effect then all the mobs harmonized have a glow around them when you cast it.<br>If it works, or fails, it does not aggro the mob.<br>It can only be cast in outdoor zones.<br>It does not totally remove the aggro radius, it only reduces it, so if you pull one mob right past another one it will add to the pull.<br><br>A good place to practice using harmony is at orc 2 in east commons, as if you get it wrong you are close to the west commons zone.<br><br>For more info try:<br><a href="http://www.eqdruids.com/tactics/tactics_harmony.htm" target=_new>http://www.eqdruids.com/tactics/tactics_harmony.htm</a></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
