	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f101665904580404>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=8&mid=101665904580404>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=101665904580404>RE: Stragies? Solo? Grouping?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=101665904580404#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Mar 20th 4:20 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=147247><span id=Sage>Hobenroby</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>85 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I am still new to the game myself (my main is an 18th level Druid at the moment) but I have learned a few things so far.<br><br>Druids in my experience are used in groups for:<br><br>Back up healers (cleric's heals are always better tho)<br><br>Our Snare helps keep the mob from running away and pulling its friends, Also it is more efficient and is resisted less than root.<br><br>Our Damage shield is very helpful when cast on the main tank (or whatever group member is being attacked!) everytime the mob hits it will be damaged. This adds up. Do this as soon as he/she pulls.<br><br>DOT is helpful against red mobs but is costly mana wise.<br><br>we can use snare and panic animal to attack red mobs and our tanks take very little damage. The mob runs away slowly and you kick its butt.(this works well solo too!)<br><br>Druids usually dont have high HP or AC so be careful about getting into melee especially at higher levels where mobs hit HARD!<br><br>I also make &quot;Hot keys&quot; that will communicate what i'm doing to the group. That way 2 druids or healers wont be wasting precious mana healing the same person or casting damage shield on the same person. Time is of the essence! Also you can be creative and have fun with these.<br><br>/gsay %t has new shoes and lunch money! Lets get em!<br><br>/gsay %t gets the spirit of wolf!<br><br><br>You can find info on hot keys somewhere on this site I think. but here is a breif explanation.<br><br>Click on &quot;socials&quot;<br>right click on a blank slot <br>In the open window give the new hotkey a name in the top slot <br>type the command in the bottom area like this:<br><br>/gsay %t has a damage shield<br><br>whatever you have targetted&nbsp;&nbsp;(%t) will be inserted in the message. <br><br>This message will then be in group chat.<br><br>Hope this wasnt too confusing.<br><br>Have fun!<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Venerable Hobenroby Thistlefoot<br>Hierophant<br>Cazic Thule Server</td></tr>
