	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=63996><span id=Scholar>Lord chking</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>79 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.42]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Alteration, in my opinion, is the way to go. It saves you on ports, healing, and buffs -- the meat of a druid's career. However, if you're a nuking druid or a kiter, evocation or conjuration may be for you. I let Tunare and Fate decide, and just put one point in each and cast as I normally did. As I guessed, Alteration bubbled to the top and hit 50 before the others did. But, don't worry if you regret your choice later on -- there is an easy quest that will reset your specializations and allow you to choose again:<br><br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=711" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=711</a><br><br>Happy hunting!</p>&nbsp;<br>-- <br>Aybara the Wookiee Swordsman on Tempest<br>Moloch the Trandoshan Master Marksman on Radiant<br>Vicktar the Mon Calamari Master Artisan on Intrepid</td></tr>
