	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Apr 10th 10:36 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=141592><span id=Scholar>dabrock</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>72 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.93]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Actually there is only one server that allows you to item loot after a PvP and I think it is Rallos Zek which is a free for all PvP server (check everquestlive.com for details on PvP here <a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/stats/sullonzek.jsp" target=_new>http://everquest.station.sony.com/stats/sullonzek.jsp</a>). The other PvP servers are team oriented by race or diety and do not allow looting other than coins. If you want to be a PvP'er I would avoid Monk and Warrior, and even rogues at higher at higher levels, because they suffer huge disadvantages to casters who can levitate, blind, mez, slow, snare, root, shadow step etc. If you want a good PvP class Druid, Necro, SK, mage, and chanter have some great advantages. Bards and Paladins are not the best PvP killers, but are hard to kill, especially by pure melee classes (monk, warrior, rogue). <br><br>Shortie rogues are very popular lower and mid level PvP'ers because of they are slippery, hard to see, and BS is dangerous. If you are in popular lower areas like CB always keep an eye on them since they are often the class of choice of PvP'ers at that level range.<br><br>But above all remember that PvP is not the be all and end all of these servers. Choose the class you want and play it. Joining a good guild is vital to your well being on PvP servers. You might find that you either love or hate PvP servers depending on your personality.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Apr 10 12:49:39 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
