	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=95215><span id= >Kothall</span></a><br><span id=notbold>105 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.92]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Mine is done fairly easy.&nbsp;&nbsp;Flip to pages 30+ and that is where all my old, out of date spells start (I move them there as I go).<br><br>Pages 1 and 2 are my stock spells that I almost always load -- <br>     Personal Protect<br>     Skin<br>     Str buff<br>     Heal<br>     Root <br>     Snare<br>     DOT<br>     DD <br>     SoW<br>     Wolf Form<br><br>Pages 3 and 4 are my more single target buff type spells (forgive me, at my level, I have more variety and need to load slightly differently than you may).<br><br>     Regen<br>     Damage Shield<br>     Gate<br>     Bind<br>     Water Breathing<br>     Leviatate<br>     Cure Poison<br>     Cure Disease<br>     Secondary DOT<br>     Secondary DD (Fury of Air)<br><br>Page 5 is all my resists:<br>     Magic<br>     Poison<br>     Disease<br>     Fire<br>     Cold<br><br>Page 6 are my group buffs (you may not have many at your level but...)<br>     Regen<br>     Damage Shield<br>     Skin<br>     SoW<br>     Wolf Form<br><br>Pages 7, 8 and 9 are my Ring spells.<br><br>Page 10 is miscelaneous spells (AoE's, etc...)<br><br>Pages 11, 12, 13 and 14 are my Group Port spells.<br><br>So on and so forth...<br><br>As I get a new generation of spell, I move my older ones back out of the way.  There is a tad bit of a mix up with some of my spells being as Post 50 DOTs and pre-50's stack.  Plus I can't use post 50 buffs on lowbies so I have a few of the older gen in earlier pages because I get a lot of requests on them but this should give you an idea on how you may want to order your book.<br><br>Best bet is to get a few more answers and then reorg your book to best suite your needs.<br><br>Kothall Landrunner<br>55th Preserver -- Povar server.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
