	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=8&mid=101659902177430>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=101659902177430>RE: A little help of the druid kind</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=101659902177430#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Mar 19th 11:39 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=62758><span id= >dcovill</span></a><br><span id=notbold>3 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I'm a 17 halfling, and moved to the Karanas at 16.<br>1. Travelling between RV and the Karanas is too hard at this level, easier if you get bound at the bank in S.Qeynos.<br><br>2. I'm working almost exclusively in WK.&nbsp;&nbsp;For experience, work the scarecrows on the Miller farm.  Great place to practice kiting and try out your different spells.  (Treeform is great here.)<br><br>3. For loot, try the bandits.  They're easy to kill, have bronze weapons, and drop sashes you can turn in in SQ for 2-3 plat each.<br><br>The shops near the guard post at the road to Miller farm give very good prices, at least as good as in SQ.<br><br>Alternative: take the boat to Erud's Crossing, get off and spend a couple (EQ) days killing wisps.  I made 90 pp there in 2 evenings.<br><br>Danco - Halfling druid 17</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
