	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=131731><span id= >rasmuz</span></a><br><span id=notbold>7 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I would highly recommend ye obtains a magikal weapon, (bloodforge hammer quest - or take the boat to Faydwer on a weekend primetime and wait for an auction in Kelethin ye should be able to pick up a scimitar for around 10 plat, but ye would be glad to pays 25 when ye get the loots) Gets ye magikal weapon and hunt wisps in east and west commons.&nbsp;&nbsp;Save the greater lightstones, sell the lightstones to a friendly merchant and destroy the burned out lightstones.  When yer packs is so heavy that ye can barley lug em about no more takes them to de gypsies in Oasis of Mar just south of the Northern Desert of Ro.  DO NOT SELL them to the gypsie wench GIVE them to her one at a time and make sure ye have got an empty slot.  Take the book she gives ya and sell it right back to her you will be plenty rich in no times.  This Oasis of Mar aint a very friendly place watch out fer de sandy giants and such and don't linger long.  When yer bored to tears wit de wispses and feeling adventurous take yer ward summoned, camoflage, and endure fire spells and get ye to Lavastorm Mountains, yer prey there is the elementals, fire imps and lava crawlers they is summoned and yer spell does a heap o damage on em.  Getting to Lavastorm means going thru Nektulos Forest get yer camoflage on and hug de left wall on yer way in when ye comes to the river swim across and hug the border tween the green stuff and the rocks afore long ye find the entrance to Lavastorm and can roll up the exp.<br>Dats what I dids and it worksed for me.  If ye are sociable types and like groups the dervish camps in Northern Desert of Ro is good loot and good exp too, just don't upset Dorn B Dyn at Derv 1, he gotsa hot temper and lies likea  cheap rug if ye cons him.  If ye are solos type ye can try derv 3 in the southwest corner, ye have to harmonyize them to pull em and ye may want a little help with the thugs but the rest should be ok long as ye don't pull more'n one ata time, if ye do get into troubles just run south to the border.  Good lucks to ye all.<br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Mar 19 11:40:02 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
