	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=95215><span id= >Kothall</span></a><br><span id=notbold>105 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.92]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>At 16th level it can be a tad rough getting going but try working on exp first.&nbsp;&nbsp;Eastern Karana is good for spider hunting.  Collect the silk.<br><br>Get stacks of silk and sell to other players that show up.  Same with any LQ, MQ and HQ pelts you get while hunting there.  You can do rather nicely on this stuff.  One idea is to get yourself a sewing kit.  Convert the silk to swatches as you hunt (build skill from NOTHING and never fails).  Swatches stack better and sell nicely.<br><br>You can solo in Eastern Karana from around your level up through your low 20's.  Higher level silk hunters there are quite willing to buff you in return for silk as well as buying it from you.  When selling, it never hurts to ask for a buff or 2 (can be concidered part of the transaction -- you can even tell them that as well &lt;grin&gt;)<br><br>Hope this helps,</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
