	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=52194><span id= >Sir Rexz</span></a><br><span id=notbold>183 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Halflings are the best race. They got the highest stats in all the most critical areas. Your only drawback is you won't win any beauty pageant. A Druid is a priest class just like a Cleric and Shaman so wisdom is king (Don't put any points into intelligence). The remaining +5 bonus points must go into stamina. Logically you would think putting your +5 bonus into strenght since all druids start off kinda weak. Higher strenght will help you as at lower levels because all characters at low level are really melee classes. &quot;Yeah, even clerics can tank at level one.&quot; Since you already have a 50 Cleric, I'm sure you know that Druids don't tank at higher levels so strenght is not a huge requirement. With higher stamina, you increase your druid's hitpoints and how hard you get hit by mobs. That become important when you're the healer in a group or kiting when you solo. In adddition, it's much easier to get strenght items compared to stamina items so your strenght will go up faster as you start twinking your druid. A good example is the Velium Ruby Veil for your face slot (+8 Wisdom, +8 Strenght). <br><br>Tairad 50 Ranger<br>Rexzi 44 Bard<br>Axze 43 Warrior<br>Dexz 42 Cleric<br>Arexz 37 Druid<br>Rexz 16 Wizard<br>Lexzi 12 Monk<br><br> </p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
